            <h4 class="text-gradient text-info mb-0">TNYIEDP – Tamil Nadu Young Innovators and Entrepreneurship Development Programme </h4>
            <h4 class="mb-4">by EDII, Govt. of TN</h4>
            <p>Under the IEDP project initiated by the Entrepreneurship Development and Innovation Institute (EDII), Tamil Nadu, CED has been an active nodal centre, driving innovation-based entrepreneurship among young minds. Through this project, students and faculty were provided financial assistance, capacity-building workshops, and mentoring to take forward their entrepreneurial aspirations. CED coordinated the implementation, selection of viable ideas, and ensured effective utilization of grant support.
<br/><br/>Presently, CED Anna University received this recognition on 16 July 2025 from Hon'ble Minister for MSME Thiru. T.M. Anbarasan - a 5 year partnership from EDII TN for implementing TNYIEDP (TamilNadu Youth Innovation and Entrepreneurship Development Programme) in all HEIs of Chennai District. Accompanied by Thiru. Ambalavanan Ramaswamy IAAS, Director, EDII-TN and Dr. Atul Anand IAS, Additional Chief Secretary to Government, MSME, TN. 
<br/><br/>The initiative aims at helping students from 2,000 higher education institutions annually, and will be implemented with an outlay of ₹19.57 crore over five years. It targets training 30.5 lakh students in entrepreneurship and innovation.
</p>
